[[Scotland national rugby union team|Scotland]], [[Ireland national rugby union team|Ireland]] and [[France national rugby union team|France]] had preceded [[England national rugby union team|England]] in embarking short tours to the [[Southern Hemisphere]], and the [[Rugby Football Union|RFU]] can be criticised for not having understood that an itineerary of six hard matches including three [[Test match (rugby union)|Test Matches]] in a mere 18 days is somewhat severe, especially when 2 Test Matches, against different countries, fall within 4 days at the end of the trip.
